---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - UK Demographics"
  description="How ukdemographics.co.uk handles your data. No cookies. No tracking. No personal data collected."
>
  <article class="legal-page shell">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: 11 April 2026</p>

    <p class="legal-intro">
      ukdemographics.co.uk is an independent demographic research project by Tom Pickup.
      This policy explains what happens to your data when you visit this site.
    </p>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        This site does not use cookies. It does not use analytics. It does not collect
        your email address. It does not require you to create an account. I do not
        know who you are when you visit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>What data is processed</h2>
      <p>
        When you visit any page, your browser automatically sends technical
        information to the servers that host this site. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your IP address</li>
        <li>The page you requested</li>
        <li>Your browser type and operating system</li>
        <li>The page that referred you here (if any)</li>
        <li>The date and time of your visit</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is processed by GitHub Pages and Cloudflare, which host and serve this
        website. They process this data to deliver the page to your browser,
        protect against attacks, and maintain service performance. I do not have
        access to individual server logs or IP addresses.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cloudflare privacy policy: <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a><br>
        GitHub privacy statement: <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">docs.github.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This site sets no cookies. It uses no analytics scripts, no tracking pixels,
        no fingerprinting, and no advertising technology. There are no third-party
        scripts loaded. There is no cookie banner because there are no cookies to consent to.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site does not use localStorage, sessionStorage, or any other browser
        storage technology.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Fonts</h2>
      <p>
        All fonts are self-hosted on ukdemographics.co.uk via Fontsource. No external
        font services (such as Google Fonts) are contacted when you visit this site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Embedded content</h2>
      <p>
        Some pages embed video content from YouTube (using the privacy-enhanced
        youtube-nocookie.com domain). YouTube may set its own cookies and collect
        data when you choose to play embedded content. Each embed is clearly marked.
        I have no control over YouTube's data processing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Lawful basis</h2>
      <p>
        The limited data processing described above (serving web pages via hosting
        infrastructure) is carried out under UK GDPR Article 6(1)(f) - legitimate
        interests. The legitimate interest is operating a publicly accessible website.
        Given the minimal data involved and the complete absence of tracking, this
        processing does not override your rights and freedoms.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to any personal data held about you</li>
        <li>Request correction or deletion of that data</li>
        <li>Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        In practice, I hold no personal data about visitors. If you contact me
        with a request, I will confirm this within one calendar month.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        Tom Pickup<br>
        Burnley, Lancashire, England<br>
        Contact: via the methodology page or through the public channels listed on the site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Supervisory authority</h2>
      <p>
        Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)<br>
        Wycliffe House, Water Lane, Wilmslow, Cheshire SK9 5AF<br>
        <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a> - Tel: 0303 123 1113
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        I may update this policy if the site's infrastructure changes. The "last
        updated" date at the top will reflect any changes.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .legal-page h1 {
    font-family: "Sora", sans-serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .legal-section h2 {
    font-family: "Sora", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .legal-section p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-section ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-section li {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
